Project Overview
This project is a Library Management System developed using Python. It allows users to manage library books through a simple menu-driven interface. The program supports operations such as adding books, viewing available books, issuing books to students, returning books, and searching for books.
Each book is stored with a Book ID, Book Name, and status (Available or Issued). When a book is issued, the system records the student name and the number of days the book is issued. If the book is returned late, the program calculates a fine amount.
The program runs continuously until the user selects the exit option.

Objectives
Build a simple Library Management System using Python
Understand menu-driven programming
Practice functions, loops, and conditional statements
Manage book records using lists and dictionaries

Implement issue and return book logic
Tools & Technologies
Python 3
VS Code / IDLE

Project Description
The system displays a menu with different library operations. The user can select an option to perform tasks such as adding books, issuing books, returning books, or searching for books.
Each function performs a specific task, making the code organized and easy to understand.
The program stores book data in a list using dictionaries to keep track of details like book ID, book name, issue status, and student information.
This project helps beginners understand how to build a simple management system using core Python concepts.

Key Concepts Used
This project demonstrates several important Python concepts:
Functions
Lists and dictionaries
While loops
Conditional statements (if-elif-else)
User input handling
Menu-driven programming

Algorithm
Start the program
Display the library management menu
Read the user’s choice
Perform the selected operation:
Add book
View books
Issue book
Return book
Search book
Update book status and student information if required
Display results or messages to the user
Repeat until the user selects Exit

Features
Menu-based user interaction
Add books with Book ID and name
View all books and their availability status
Issue books to students
Return books with fine calculation
Search books by name
Continuous execution until exit

Result
The Library Management System successfully performs all library operations including adding books, issuing books, returning books, and searching for books through a simple menu-driven interface.

Conclusion
This mini project demonstrates how Python can be used to develop a basic management system using functions, loops, and data structures. It helps beginners understand how real-world systems such as libraries can be implemented using simple programming logic.
